Language name: AKAWAIO
Language number: 6853
Alternate names: 
Classification: South American, Macro-Carib
Comments: Akawaio is spoken in the Mazanini river basin in 
Guyana. /s,z/ are palato-alveolar affricates adjacent to 
/i/.

Sources: 

Edwards, W.F. 1978. Some synchronic and diachronic aspects 
of Akawaio phonology. Anthropological Linguistics 20: 
77-84.